Also, I missed one of your questions:<br>
&quot;Do thieves have restrictions on stealth? (i.e. how many steps you can walk while hidden.)&quot;<br>
<br>
Stealth is very powerful.  It's more like a magical ability than literally hiding.  While stealthed, you are either transparent or totally invisible, depending on whether the person in question successfully &quot;sees&quot; you or not.  Monsters cannot see you while stealthed, but will reveal (un-stealth) you if they are near or higher than your level and looking right at you.  You can make them turn around with Distraction.  You move slower while stealthed (walk-speed).  Attacking or being attacked causes you to un-stealth.  The actual detect rate goes something like this:<br>
<br>
At lower levels (&lt;20) with a good spec in stealth, most people close to your level will be able to see you (transparent) at several paces.  People much higher level than you will be able to see you (transparent) from fairly far away.<br>
<br>
At medium levels (20-35ish) with a good spec in stealth, people your level or lower will only see you if they are practically standing on top of you, higher level than you will see you from several paces away.<br>
<br>
At high levels (40+) with a good spec in stealth, pretty much only people higher than you will see you, and then only if they are practically standing on top of you.<br>
<br>
Assassin classes get an ability called Detect Hidden, which either wasn't working or wasn't doing much at all.  In the upcoming patch they are increasing the range that people with Detect Hidden (assassins) can see stealthed people (archers, assassins, and minstrels), but I don't know how much of an impact that will have.<br>
<br>
